<?php $__env->startSection('content'); ?><p>She is known for her sizzling style choices.   </p>

<p>But Nicole Scherzinger proved she could embrace the cold as she submerged herself in a 3°C (37.4F) ice bath alongside her boyfriend Thom Evans on Saturday.</p>

<p>The Pussycat Dolls star, 42, donned a metallic swimsuit as she channelled her inner healing mode by sitting in a bath surrounded by floating ice cubes.</p>

<p>Scroll down for video </p>

<p>Chill: Nicole Scherzinger, 42, embraced the cold as she submerged herself in a 3°C (37.4F) ice bath alongside her beau Thom Evans on Saturday</p>

<p>Nicole wore a metallic silver swimsuit which sculpted her hourglass figure as she relaxed in the icy water at Remedy Place in California. </p>

<p>The songstress pinned her brunette locks into a sleek topknot and went without a scrap of makeup for the treatment which claims to 'increase endorphins'. </p>

<p>She posted a video of herself in the tub to her Instagram, captioned: 'Whatchu know about that 3°C ice bath...' </p>

<p>Move: The singer showed off her sizzling physique in a silver metallic swimsuit as she and beau Thom slowly emerged from their ice bath</p>

<p>Meanwhile on her Instagram Story Nicole could not help but sing along to Lauren Daigle which was playing during her treatment with Thom in an ice bath next to her. </p>

<p>An invigorated Nicole and Thom slowly emerged from their ice bath with the singer moving her hips to LATASHÁ as she rose to her feet. </p>

<p>According to reports, Nicole is trying for a baby with her handsome beau Thom after less than a year of dating. </p>

<p>Cold: The Pussycat Dolls star channelled her inner healing mode as she sat with her eyes closed in the bath surrounded by floating ice cubes</p>

<p>In sync: Nicole could not help but sing along to Lauren Daigle before the pair emerged from their ice bath</p>

<p>The singer is said to be keen to start a family of her own with Thom, as the couple are looking to the future and intend on purchasing a property together in London.</p>

<p>A friend told The Sun: 'Thom told pals he's been taking supplements to boost fertility. Nicole and Thom are ridiculously loved-up, and have had serious conversations about everything from marriage to babies.  </p>

<p>'No one would be surprised if they had some baby news in the coming months.</p>

<p>'Thom currently lives with his brother and a housemate in London which hardly makes for a romantic love nest. They are looking to buy a house together once lockdown is over.'</p>

<p>Nicole's representatives declined to comment and MailOnline also contacted Thom's representatives at the time, who are yet to comment.    </p>

